{"questionId":"22450354","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Σ</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;to form a linear equation in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>21</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>80</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>43</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>37</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve two linear equations simultaneously for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> (one of which is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>21</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>80</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>46</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22450354","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that q-p=3, find the value of p and the value of q.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Prior learning","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}